    dc:creator "Matsunuma, Mizuki; Motomura, Hiroyuki" ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Three new species of the Indo-Pacific stingfish genus Minous (Synanceiidae: Minoinae) with redescriptions of M. trachycephalus (Bleeker 1855) and M. pictus Günther 1880" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457121>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457123>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457139>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457141>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457143>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457113>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457117>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457119> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457121>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Inner surfaces of pectoral fins in preserved specimens of Minous roseus sp. nov. (A–C) and M. trachycephalus (D–F). (A) CSIRO CA1844, holotype, 72.1 mm SL, Western Australia (right side, reversed); (B) KAUM–I. 113069, paratype, 52.8 mm SL, Western Australia; (C) NMV A29722-006, paratype, 44.2 mm SL, Western Australia; (D) RMNH.PISC. 5901, holotype, 55.9 mm SL, Indonesia; (E) KAUM–I. 33284, 70.4 mm SL, Gulf of Thailand; (F) BMNH 1879.5.14.372, paralectotype of M. pictus, 36.6 mm SL, Arafura Sea. Photos: Gota Ogihara (A, C and D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457121/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457123>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Distributional maps of Minous trachycephalus (purple squares); M. groeneveldi sp. nov. (yellow stars); M. roseus sp. nov. (blue circles); M. andriashevi (gray downward triangles); M. pictus (yellow upward triangles); and M. radiatus sp. nov. (green diamonds). White arrowheads indicate type localities. Black arrowheads indicate photographic records (Lembeh Strait, North Sulawesi, Indonesia)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457123/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457139>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Relationships of (A) head length; (B) snout length; (C) interorbital width at mid-orbit; and (D) 1st dorsal-fin spine length (all as % of standard length) to standard length (mm) in Minous roseus sp. nov. (blue circles), M. groeneveldi sp. nov. (yellow star, holotype), M. trachycephalus (purple squares) and M. pusillus (black crosses). Open arrowhead indicates paralectotype of M. pictus (= M. trachycephalus). Closed arrowheads indicate holotypes of M. roseus and M. trachycephalus, and lectotype of M. pusillus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457139/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457141>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Relationships of (A) head depth; (B) interorbital width at preocular spine base; and (C) 2nd dorsal-fin spine length (all as % of standard length) to standard length (mm) in Minous roseus sp. nov. (blue circles), M. groeneveldi sp. nov. (yellow star, holotype) and M. trachycephalus (purple squares). Open and closed arrowheads indicate paralectotype of M. pictus (= M. trachycephalus) and holotype of M. roseus, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457141/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457143>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Lateral view of head (A, C, G) and lacrimal spines (semi-schematic) in Minous groeneveldi sp. nov. (A, B), M. roseus sp. nov. (C–F) and M. trachycephalus (G–K). (A, B) NTM S.11031-002, holotype, 77.7 mm SL, Indonesia; (C, D) CSIRO CA1844, holotype, 72.1 mm SL, Western Australia; (E) CSIRO CA1589, paratype, 53.9 mm SL, Western Australia; (F) NMV A29660-012, paratype, 33.5 mm SL, Western Australia; (G) RMNH.PISC. 5901, holotype, 55.9 mm SL, Indonesia; (H) KAUM–I. 33284, 70.4 mm SL, Thailand (Gulf of Thailand); (I) KAUM–I. 49280, 55.2 mm SL, Malaysia (Borneo); (J) KAUM–I. 33288, 55.7 mm SL, Thailand (Andaman Sea); (K) BMNH 1879.5.14.372, paralectotype of M. pictus, 36.6 mm SL, Arafura Sea. Red dotted lines (in A and C) indicate horizontal line through top of snout bulge. Red and blue arrowheads indicate anterior and posterior lacrimal spines, respectively. Bars indicate 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457143/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457113>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Preserved specimens of Minous roseus sp. nov. at different growth stages. (A) CSIRO CA1844, holotype, 72.1 mm SL, Western Australia; (B–C) NTM S.13974-005, paratype, 63.9 mm SL, Western Australia; (D) CSIRO CA1576, paratype, 53.2 mm SL, Western Australia; (E) CSIRO CA1576, paratype, 53.2 mm SL, Western Australia; (F) CAS 60400, 40.2 mm SL, Maldives; (G) AMS I.22832-012, paratype, 32.8 mm SL, Western Australia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457113/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457117>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Fresh specimens of Minous roseus sp. nov.—lateral views (A, C);—pectoral fin inner surface (B). (A–B) CSIRO CA1844, holotype, 72.1 mm SL, Western Australia; (C) CSIRO CA1576, paratype, 53.2 mm SL, Western Australia. Photos: CSIRO." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457117/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457119>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Underwater photographs of Minous roseus sp. nov. from Lembeh Strait, North Sulawesi, Indonesia. Photos: Johnny Braun." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457119/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

